<ContentLayout 
	title="Accessibility Statement"
	description="Learn about WhyA11y's commitment to web accessibility and how we ensure our site is usable by everyone."
>
	<h1>Accessibility Statement</h1>
	
	<p><strong>WhyA11y is committed to ensuring digital accessibility for people with disabilities.</strong> We are continually improving the user experience for everyone and applying the relevant accessibility standards.</p>

	<h2>Conformance Status</h2>
	
	<p>The Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) defines requirements for designers and developers to improve accessibility for people with disabilities. It defines three levels of conformance: Level A, Level AA, and Level AAA.</p>
	
	<p>WhyA11y is <strong>partially conformant</strong> with <strong>WCAG 2.1 level AA</strong>. Partially conformant means that some parts of the content do not fully conform to the accessibility standard.</p>

	<h2>Accessibility Features</h2>
	
	<p>Our website includes the following accessibility features:</p>
	
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Semantic HTML:</strong> Proper use of heading hierarchy, lists, and semantic elements</li>
		<li><strong>Keyboard Navigation:</strong> All functionality accessible via keyboard</li>
		<li><strong>Skip Links:</strong> Quick navigation to main content, navigation, and footer</li>
		<li><strong>Focus Indicators:</strong> Clear visual focus indicators for all interactive elements</li>
		<li><strong>Color Contrast:</strong> WCAG AA compliant color contrast ratios</li>
		<li><strong>Alternative Text:</strong> Descriptive alt text for images</li>
		<li><strong>ARIA Labels:</strong> Proper ARIA attributes for enhanced screen reader support</li>
		<li><strong>Responsive Design:</strong> Accessible across all device sizes</li>
		<li><strong>Dark/Light Mode:</strong> Theme switching with proper contrast</li>
		<li><strong>Reduced Motion:</strong> Respects user's motion preferences</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Known Issues</h2>
	
	<p>We are aware of the following accessibility issues and are working to resolve them:</p>
	
	<ul>
		<li>Some code examples may need additional language attributes for better screen reader support</li>
		<li>Complex interactive elements may benefit from additional ARIA live regions</li>
		<li>Search functionality (when implemented) will need comprehensive accessibility testing</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Compatibility</h2>
	
	<p>WhyA11y is designed to be compatible with the following assistive technologies:</p>
	
	<ul>
		<li>Screen readers (NVDA, JAWS, VoiceOver, TalkBack)</li>
		<li>Screen magnification software</li>
		<li>Speech recognition software</li>
		<li>Keyboard-only navigation</li>
		<li>High contrast mode</li>
		<li>Reduced motion preferences</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Testing</h2>
	
	<p>We test our website for accessibility using:</p>
	
	<ul>
		<li>Automated testing tools (axe-core, Lighthouse)</li>
		<li>Manual keyboard navigation testing</li>
		<li>Screen reader testing</li>
		<li>Color contrast analysis</li>
		<li>Mobile accessibility testing</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Feedback and Contact</h2>
	
	<p>We welcome your feedback on the accessibility of WhyA11y. Please let us know if you encounter accessibility barriers:</p>
	
	<ul>
		<li>Email: <a href="mailto:hello@whya11y.com">hello@whya11y.com</a></li>
		<li>Subject line: "Accessibility Feedback"</li>
	</ul>
	
	<p>We try to respond to accessibility feedback within 2 business days.</p>

	<h2>Technical Specifications</h2>
	
	<p>Accessibility of WhyA11y relies on the following technologies to work with the particular combination of web browser and any assistive technologies or plugins installed on your computer:</p>
	
	<ul>
		<li>HTML</li>
		<li>CSS</li>
		<li>JavaScript</li>
		<li>WAI-ARIA</li>
	</ul>
	
	<p>These technologies are relied upon for conformance with the accessibility standards used.</p>

	<h2>Assessment Methods</h2>
	
	<p>WhyA11y assessed the accessibility of our website by the following approaches:</p>
	
	<ul>
		<li>Self-evaluation using automated testing tools</li>
		<li>Manual testing with keyboard navigation</li>
		<li>Screen reader testing</li>
		<li>Mobile device testing</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Formal Complaints</h2>
	
	<p>If you are not satisfied with our response to your accessibility feedback, you may file a formal complaint by contacting us at <a href="mailto:hello@whya11y.com">hello@whya11y.com</a>.</p>

	<h2>Continuous Improvement</h2>
	
	<p>We are committed to continuously improving the accessibility of our website. This includes:</p>
	
	<ul>
		<li>Regular accessibility audits</li>
		<li>User feedback integration</li>
		<li>Staying updated with accessibility standards</li>
		<li>Training on accessibility best practices</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Date</h2>
	
	<p>This statement was created on <time datetime="2025-01-27">January 27, 2025</time> and will be reviewed and updated regularly.</p>

